Author: dumbdumbidiotbitch
Text: This kind of thinking is how my disordered eating began, but trust me, now matter how much you weigh you’re still going to be you and you’re still going to have those demons.... I’ve lost 25 pounds and I still hate myself and think I’m the biggest stupidest ugliest idiot in the world

Author: -bluehoney-
Text: This sounds pretty disordered my dude.  But, if it helps, those things aren’t the fault of your weight and you don’t need to punish yourself this way.   Especially if you’re new to having these thoughts and feelings, quit while you’re ahead. It absolutely only gets worse and more irrational and miserable from here.
